result.name: Panera Bread

reviews.text: So mean! Meanest Panera I’ve ever been to. Food was not great, below average but I barely touched it because they were just rude. Horrible people working. Management made me more upset than workers , overall horrible experience. Don’t come here. Also Mac was just cheese soup. Already handled food before we got it.

I waited a little long for my order but it was during a busy time and the girl behind the counter  (I wish I got her name!) could not have been more polite and apologetic to me which was completely unnecessary because they make everything to order and I know they had a rush! It was worth the wait because as usual the sandwiches were delicious! Always enjoy their fresh salads too!

Does this look like a wrap? It is barely folded.  It doesn't help a customer for takeout to get this poorly made pile of food to try to eat it on the go.
Please train your people how to do a good job at making your simple items.

Over priced with exceptionally small portions.  Git the teriyaki bowl and it looked like a kids portion and cost about $12. The manager did speak to me and offered to get me something else to satisfy my appetite, which I thought was cool! One pic is of the plate, another of the misleading poster yo advertise the bowl

Horrible. All I have to say is the management and staff are rude. I got a refund for Mac and cheese because it looked like cheese water and a few noodles. I politely asked for a new one…and was denied!!!! Couldn’t believe it. Then I asked for a refund and as the manager walked over, she muttered under her breath about how much she hated wasting food like the Mac and cheese that they gave me. Then proceeded to give me a CASH refund for an ONLINE ORDER. Was super sarcastic with me, and showed no kindness whatsoever. Just overall a bad experience with people who clearly don’t know what they’re doing or haven’t had a visit from corporate in a while… I’m in my 20s and pretty relaxed as a person but I couldn’t even believe this experience. Never coming here again. Not like other paneras, trust me and just drive the extra 10 minutes to the one on bald hill.
